- The integer array parameter `distance` contains the distances between all pairs of neighboring bus stops.
- The integer parameter `start` represents the starting bus stop.
- The integer parameter `destination` represents the destination bus stop.
- The integer result is the shortest distance between the starting bus stop and the destination bus stop.
- The integer result is greater than or equal to 0.
- The integer result is less than or equal to the sum of all distances in the `distance` array.